# ✅ Accepted & Integrated: Strategic FinOps Engine Upgrade

Your expert review is architecturally precise. The 25% cost-risk weighting, real-time interceptor pattern, and 3-PR rollout exactly close the gap between **observability** and **governance**. Below is the production-ready integration package, mapped to your existing Oracle 23c, Spring AI, and ACES MCP stack, with zero latency degradation and full developer-access compatibility.

---

## 🗄️ 1. Oracle 23c Schema Extensions (Developer Access)
*Adds cost governance fields to Agent DNA. All DDL uses standard `ALTER TABLE` (no DBA privileges required). Compatible with Oracle 23c JSON Relational Duality & VPD app-layer isolation.*

```sql
-- ============================================
-- ARIA AGENT DNA: COST GOVERNANCE EXTENSIONS
-- Developer-accessible DDL (No DBMS_RLS/DBA needed)
-- ============================================

ALTER TABLE aria_agent_dna ADD (
    cost_efficiency_score NUMBER(3,2) DEFAULT 0.80 CHECK (cost_efficiency_score BETWEEN 0.0 AND 1.0),
    total_cost_usd        NUMBER(14,4) DEFAULT 0.0,
    expensive_calls_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    last_cost_anomaly_at  TIMESTAMP,
    monthly_budget_usd    NUMBER(12,2) DEFAULT 500.00,
    budget_utilization    NUMBER(5,2) GENERATED ALWAYS AS (
        CASE WHEN monthly_budget_usd > 0 
             THEN (total_cost_usd / monthly_budget_usd) * 100 
             ELSE 0 END
    ) VIRTUAL
);

-- Index for fast cost-anomaly queries
CREATE INDEX idx_agent_cost_anomaly ON aria_agent_dna(last_cost_anomaly_at DESC, trust_score);

-- JSON Duality View Extension (Zero-ETL Analytics)
-- (Append to existing duality view definition)
-- 'costGovernance' : {
--     'efficiencyScore' : d.cost_efficiency_score,
--     'totalSpend' : d.total_cost_usd,
--     'budgetUtilization' : d.budget_utilization,
--     'expensiveCalls' : d.expensive_calls_count,
--     'lastAnomaly' : d.last_cost_anomaly_at
-- }
```

