## 🚀 4. 3-PR Execution Plan (Stack-Aligned)
*Mapped to Spring Boot 3.3, Spring AI 1.0, Oracle 23c, ACES MCP. Zero breaking changes.*

| PR # | Scope | Files to Change | Acceptance Test |
|------|-------|-----------------|-----------------|
| **1** | Data Capture & Interceptor | `aria-cost-interceptor/` (new module), `AgentDnaRepository.java`, `PricingCatalog.java` | Every LLM/tool call writes a `cost_metric` row to Oracle with `trace_id`. Pre-check latency ≤ 8ms. |
| **2** | Real-Time Signal & Stage 5 | `CostRiskAdvisor.java`, `SignalIngestor.java`, `RiskScoringEngine.java` | Inject `CostSignal` into Stage 5. Mock "expensive" call changes ARIA verdict from `ALLOW` → `REQUIRES_APPROVAL`. |
| **3** | Trust Impact & Async Update | `TrustScoreEngine.java`, `AgentDnaService.java`, `CostPostProcessor.java` | Run agent through 10 "inefficient" calls. Verify `trust_score` drops 0.70 → 0.55, `trend` → `DECLINING`, async update completes < 50ms post-stream. |

